  "@id": "https://bio.tools/signal_peptides_structure_modeling_services",
  "@type": "sc:SoftwareApplication",
  "dcterms:conformsTo": "https://bioschemas.org/profiles/ComputationalTool/0.6-DRAFT",
  "sc:description": "Signal peptides are short sequences of amino acids, typically between 15 and 30 residues long, found at the N-terminal of proteins. They serve a critical function in directing the transport of proteins throughout the cell. CD ComputaBio offers a comprehensive suite of services dedicated to supporting your signal peptides discovery initiatives.",
